If we open $n$ number of doors what's the probability of switch

1 car + 6 goats
given $1/7$ per door
open 5 doors: $6/7$
open 3 doors: $6/7 * 1/3 = 2/7$

*we will do a follow up*

*Follow up time!...*

1 car, 2 goats
We'll use [[Conditional Probability|Conditional Probability]]

I pick door #1 \\\\\ host action
Case 1: C G G \\\\\\ D2 or D3 w/ Prob. 1/2
Case 2: G C G \\\\\\ D3 w/ prob. 1
Case 3: G G C \\\\\\ D2 w/prob. 1

$$
\begin{align*}
P(\text{Case }1|D3)&= \frac{P(\text{Case }1 \text{ and } D3)}{P(D3)}\\
&= \frac{P(D3|\text{Case }1)\cdot P(\text{Case }1)}{P(D3|\text{Case 1})P(\text{Case }1) + P(D3|\text{Case 2})P(\text{Case 2}) + P(D3|\text{Case 3})P(\text{Case 3})}\\
&= \frac{\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)}{\left(\frac{1}{2}\right)\left(\frac{1}{3}\right) + (1)\left(\frac{1}{3}\right) + (0)\left(\frac{1}{3}\right)}\\
&= \frac{1}{3}
\end{align*}
$$


More general cases:
$n$ doors, $k$ opened (at the same time)

$n=6,k=2$

Say we pick door \#1
unopened doors have probabilities: $\frac{5}{6}\times \frac{1}{3} = \frac{5}{18}$
